00:58:09,359 --> 00:58:13,440
Um and that is a very particular set of feelings.

841
00:58:13,440 --> 00:58:21,680
Um, and the first thing, you know, I learned when someone makes you a manager or when you take a job as a leader inside a company,

842
00:58:21,680 --> 00:58:25,760
you really do feel like like, uhoh, like who gave me this job?

843
00:58:25,760 --> 00:58:28,720
You know, and you sort of feel like you're supposed to know the answer to things.

844
00:58:28,720 --> 00:58:33,040
Like people come to you and ask questions and you're like, I'm spo I'm supposed to know,

845
00:58:33,040 --> 00:58:33,280
right?

846
00:58:33,280 --> 00:58:34,160
I'm a leader.

847
00:58:34,160 --> 00:58:35,760
I am supposed to have answers.

848
00:58:35,760 --> 00:58:45,839
And I think particularly inside of rapid change and and scale and growth, it's really important to understand that your job as a manager and a leader is not to have all the answers.

849
00:58:45,839 --> 00:58:47,440
It is not to have all the answers.

850
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:50,079
It is to get good at finding them.

851
00:58:50,079 --> 00:58:54,640
It is to get good at bringing people together to find the answers.

