01:07:50,559 --> 01:08:00,720
Something else I wanted to make sure we spend a little time on is you have another tidbit along these lines which is around putting most of your energy into high performers versus spending all your time with people that need help.

994
01:08:00,720 --> 01:08:02,240
Talk about that.

995
01:08:02,240 --> 01:08:13,440
>> You know, as a leader, as a manager, like you you're running these teams and someone's struggling um and it's very easy to get dragged into that and to to

996
01:08:13,440 --> 01:08:16,560
sort of end up spending a huge amount of energy on it.

997
01:08:16,560 --> 01:08:20,239
But high performers are actually the future of your company.

998
01:08:20,239 --> 01:08:27,679
And if you think about it and if you've spent time on it, um those are the folks where if you invest your time and energy in them,

999
01:08:27,679 --> 01:08:32,880
you're going to get the sort of like 10x return that people talk about all the time in Silicon Valley.

1000
01:08:32,880 --> 01:08:40,000
But um what I've witnessed is that most people have like a high performer and they just like leave them alone.

1001
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:44,239
They're like that person's doing well, so I'm just going to let them do their thing.

1002
01:08:44,239 --> 01:08:48,480
And what what I do when I have a high performer, that's like my favorite thing in the world,

1003
01:08:48,480 --> 01:08:57,679
is invest time and energy in them and basically build a whole system of working with them that is designed to kind of draw out potential.

1004
01:08:57,679 --> 01:09:01,120
Um, and I would say there's there's two two things here.

1005
01:09:01,120 --> 01:09:07,759
One is it's really important to realize that like our tendency is to actually spend time on low performers and it is not a good use of your time.

1006
01:09:07,759 --> 01:09:09,839
See the point about firing people.

1007
01:09:09,839 --> 01:09:20,239
But the other thing is that actively investing in and developing high performers is something that's important to get good at as a leader because that is how you kind of create these little

1008
01:09:20,239 --> 01:09:30,480
rocket ships that end up you know you'll manage someone who's just like a project manager and all of a sudden they're running a whole function inside the company eventually but it's because you took time and energy to invest in them.

1009
01:09:30,480 --> 01:09:37,279
And my basic way of doing that not to like I could go I could spend a long time on this but I would just say is I run experiments.

